{"symbol": "FAF2", "uniprot": "Q96CS3", "protein_name": "FAS-associated factor 2", "length": 445, "function": "Plays an important role in endoplasmic reticulum-associated degradation (ERAD) that mediates ubiquitin-dependent degradation of misfolded endoplasmic reticulum proteins (PubMed:18711132, PubMed:24215460). By controlling the steady-state expression of the IGF1R receptor, indirectly regulates the insulin-like growth factor receptor signaling pathway (PubMed:26692333). Recruits ATPase VCP to lipid droplets and also binds to phospholipase PNPLA2/ATGL, inhibiting PNPLA2 activity by promoting its dissociation from its ABHD5/CGI-58 activator (PubMed:23297223). This inhibits PNPLA2-mediated triacylglycerol hydrolysis and leads to inhibition of lipid droplet degradation (PubMed:23297223). Involved in stress granule disassembly: associates with ubiquitinated G3BP1 in response to heat shock, thereby promoting interaction between ubiquitinated G3BP1 and VCP, followed by G3BP1 extraction from stress granules and stress granule disassembly (PubMed:34739333)", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000113194", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.2517, "protein_drug": 0.31, "rna_drug": 0.558}, "flags": {"surface": false, "enzyme": true, "mod_aso": true, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "ASO", "winning_axis": "RNA", "quadrant": "Both viable", "best_route": "small molecule", "sm_score": "0.37", "sirna_score": "0.32", "aso_score": "0.463"}, "modality": "ASO", "structure": "data/structures/FAF2.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.383, "volume": 614.0, "residues": [96, 97, 100, 101, 103, 104, 105, 107, 108, 109]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.207, "volume": 338.0, "residues": [384, 410, 411, 412, 413, 420, 424, 428, 429]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.062, "volume": 393.7, "residues": [91, 92, 93, 95, 96, 99]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q96CS3"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "http